##Ye Qing's Wuhan Documentary: Seven changes in 17 days

Micro-signal Zhenghedao

Features introduced by Zhenghe Island, a high-end social networking platform focused on entrepreneurs.

It has been 17 days since the "closure" of the city on January 23 to the Lantern Festival. Even if I keep a diary every day, it seems like time flies.

I used to get up early, get up at 6, get to the office at 7, no traffic. Now I sleep until I wake up. I feel like I'm retiring early. Although I still have two years left.

These 17 days, can be said to be breathtaking, ups and downs, every day there are hot spots, information to the explosion. What was the most important event? What are the changes?

As one of the nine million people who remain in Wuhan, I would like to say a few words.

Ye Qing, a professor at Zhongnan University of Economics and Law and deputy director of the Hubei Provincial Bureau of Statistics, is next door to blue island

Source: Zhenghe Island (ID: Zhenghedao)

From fearlessness and panic to acceptance

It is often said that a baby is happiest because he knows nothing of danger and is carefree. Once you know what fear is, kids get scared.

Before January 20, the mentality of Wuhan people is to be in "Early Childhood" .

Under the influence of the COVID-19's judgment that "no one can pass on their knowledge to others" , the people of Wuhan still live a very comfortable life. Netizens remind people in Wuhan: You Wuhan is already an epidemic area. Wuhan people very smart to say: not so serious, experts said that will not "person to person. ".

In an interview with CCTV on the evening of January 20, Zhong Nanshan, an academician of the Chinese Academy of Engineering and the head of a high level Expert Group of the National Health Commission, said that there must be human to human transmission of the new type of pneumonia, with 14 medical staff in Wuhan infected with the virus. He also urged: If not necessary, do not go to Wuhan in the near future.

The LAST SENTENCE MAKES WUHAN PEOPLE'S HAIR STAND ON END: Isn't this the same as the 2003"SARS" saying? Is SARS going to start all over again. The people of Wuhan are afraid. However, the Wuhan people who have not been to the hospital scene still have no real feelings. At this time, medical staff, medical treatment or spread on Wechat real scene: Crowded Hospital Video, medical staff out of control vent, especially worrying. This step by step heightens our fear.

And so, the real fear began. Most of the 5M people who left Wuhan "fled" from the city at this point.

The Wuhan Government issued a notice on the evening of January 22 to impose restrictions on wearing face masks in public places. Staff members of state organs, enterprises and institutions shall wear face masks while on duty. This is an important point in time.

I myself started wearing a mask on the 21st, and only when I was out for a midday walk, not at the office. At the time, it was a little weird for people to wear masks. Now, it's normal to wear a mask.

A few days ago there was an extreme case: a man in Ningbo was infected while shopping without a mask. The process took only 15 seconds.

On the morning of the 23rd, people in Wuhan were informed of the suspension of all public transport at 10 am. On the streets of Wuhan, you can feel a palpable sense of panic. In the last 40 years, there has never been a siege. The last time Wuhan was "closed" was in 1911 when the city was Wuchang Uprising, Netizens said.

For a moment, the map showed that the highway exits were all red lines. We all know that many people want to leave Wuhan before the expressway is closed. Although the city government has repeatedly refuted rumors, stressed that will not "close the city. ". In fact, at 15:54 on the 23rd, the entrances of a total of 30 toll booths on Hubei Expressway were closed to vehicles.

Unable to go out for the New Year, people began to rush to the supermarket shopping, this is no doubt another time of great infection.

I myself had planned to spend the New Year in a haze-free house in Xianning on January 24. Now the plan was disrupted, had to stay in the city, accept the "sealed off city" such a reality.

As it turns out, "do as you're told" is always right. Especially in wartime.

The 5m who "fled" from Wuhan were more distressed than the 9M who stayed. "The Hubei people become the evil people, " "the Han people become the sick people, " "the Han people come from Wuhan, " "the people come from Beijing, " 17 years ago.

It's a real turn-on. Almost every day, a friend in Wuhan said to me, I shouldn't have come out.

From municipal and provincial support, national aid to world attention

At the beginning, people had always thought that Wuhan had abundant medical resources and sufficient material preparation to deal with several infectious patients. Now it seems that the decision-making level in Wuhan has despised the "enemy" both tactically and strategically.

Wuhan has adopted a new "7 + 7" model for fever patients in response to possible cross-infection and spread of diseases caused by disorderly medical visits.

That is to say, 7 second-level public hospitals were selected near 7 large hospitals in the urban area as designated hospitals for fever outpatient clinics. All the transferred patients and vacated wards were used to receive fever patients and treated fever patients specially.

Later it expanded to 10 + 10, still not enough. By January 29, Hubei had set up 131 designated hospitals to treat COVID-19 pneumonia patients, of which 30 were in Wuhan and 101 were in cities and states across the province. Fever clinics have been set up in 549 second-level and above medical institutions and all township hospitals in Hubei Province, where 24-hour consultation is practiced. The province has installed 11,000 isolation beds, of which 5,000 have been opened in Wuhan.

Starting from the evening of March 3, Wuhan Convention and Exhibition Center, the Wembley Arena and the living room of Wuhan were built with three square cabin hospitals. The central guidance team urgently dispatched 2,000 medical and nursing personnel from 20 provinces to arrive in Wuhan one after another, and provided medical and nursing personnel to three square cabin hospitals.

At the same time, the central isolation points for each district were raised, and places such as private hospitals, hotels, party schools and schools were requisitioned as the central isolation points for each district. As at 24:00 on February 4, there were 132 isolation points with 12,571 beds and 5,425 people of various types were centrally isolated.

In this way, fixed-point hospital and Fire Mountain Hospital, Shelter Hospital, isolation point, fever clinic, become Wuhan's four lines of defense.

There is also a big gap in material goods. As of January 31, Hubei Province can only produce 8 million medical masks, 2 million protective clothing, infrared thermometers 1,200 sets, can not meet the province's epidemic prevention needs. On the afternoon of January 22, Hubei Province plans to request urgent support from the state, allocating 40 million medical masks, 5 million protective clothing and 5,000 infrared thermometers.

At present, the contradiction between supply and demand of medical materials is still very prominent. How big is the breach? Take a look at this number.

On February 6, Wuhan needed 59,900 medical protective clothing for the day, with a daily shortfall of 41,400, a daily requirement of 119,000 medical N95 masks, a daily requirement of 56,800, and a daily requirement of 22,500 medical goggles (masks) , there were 19,200 breaches that day.

What a breach!

As people who worked in Wuhan returned home, pneumonia cases were found all over the province, and the battle quickly spread across the province and indeed the country. All places in the local fight against the epidemic at the same time, to support the strength of Hubei. To form a national support network.

The first medical team from Shanghai to Hubei was the first medical team to arrive in Wuhan. The medical team consists of 135 persons, of whom 38 are doctors, 93 are professional nurses and the rest are logistics liaison support personnel. On January 25, the first day of the Lunar New Year, they set off from Shanghai and arrived in Wuhan that afternoon.

As of February 6,99 medical teams and 9277 people from all provinces and cities have been dispatched to support Wuhan. Of these, 56 medical teams with 5,540 personnel have been stationed at designated hospitals, 4 PLA medical teams with 1,400 personnel have been stationed at Huoshenshan Hospital, 39 medical teams with 2,337 personnel have been stationed at three shelter hospitals, and 9 medical teams with 1,400 personnel are arriving one after another on July 7.

On this basis, a province helped a city in Hubei launch the model. The press conference of the Joint Prevention and Control Mechanism of the State Council was held on the afternoon of February 7, announcing that the National Health Commission has established a one-to-one support relationship among 16 provinces to support cities outside Wuhan, in the form of one province covering one city, give full support to Hubei Province to strengthen the rescue and treatment of patients.

This way, inherited the "aid Xinjiang, " "Aid Tibet, " the fine tradition, is really "a difficult eight-party support.

60 million people in Hubei will remember this list with gratitude.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Of course, Hubei needs more leadership than just health care.

A little after 23 am on the 7th, China Women's Daily, an obscure newspaper in China, announced that two important members of the central committee were coming to Hubei. When I saw it, I didn't believe it.

On the morning of the 8th, Major Media announced that comrade Wang Hesheng was appointed to the Hubei Provincial Committee and Standing Committee.

Wang Hesheng was born in June 1961. In 1984, he graduated from the Department of Health of the Tianjin Medical University. The key is that he has been deputy director of the National Health Commission and a member of the Party since March 2018; he has been on the front line of the fight against the epidemic in Wuhan since January 23. It was also a test for him.

A member of the Standing Committee of the provincial Party Committee who knows medicine has finally arrived.

I have a small goal: leaders at all levels should have deputy governors, deputy mayors and deputy county chiefs who understand medicine, even deputy directors of the National People's Congress and vice chairmen of the Chinese People's Political Consultative Conference. Governments at all levels to set up health advisory group, not only investment consultants.

This one fight the enemy (virus) , from the small south China Seafood Market, to Hankou, to Hubei Province, to the country, to the world.

As of 14:00 GMT on June 6,24 countries and regions outside China had confirmed 216 cases of pneumonia and one death from COVID-19.

In the early hours of Jan. 31, the China Standard Time declared the COVID-19 a public health emergency of international concern. At the same time, it was stressed in particular that there was no need for measures to restrict the Movement of international personnel and that who did not recommend travel restrictions.

The fight against the virus became an international effort.

As of noon on February 5,21 countries including South Korea, Japan, Thailand, Malaysia and UNICEF have donated epidemic prevention and control materials to China. At the same time, while some countries have suspended their tourist flights to China, Russian tourist companies have also formulated an assistance plan to alleviate the financial losses of Chinese tourist companies in the first place.

Cambodia's Prime Minister, Hun Sen, visited Beijing on his way to Wuhan.

A friend in need is a friend indeed.

From medical staff to workers, peasants and soldiers studying business

Not only the medical staff in Wuhan first-line struggle, the national workers, farmers, soldiers, students and businessmen in various ways to support Wuhan.

"fight to the death: from Chinese food to North Henan Small Town! " A very good article.

In the beginning of 2020, from the first basket of Shouguang vegetables was sent to Wuhan, China's "brother workers and peasants" first rushed to the front line, since then to take up the world's great responsibility with a thin body.

On January 28, more than 350 tons of quality vegetables donated by Shouguang, Shandong Province, were shipped. It takes only 17 hours and more than 1,000 kilometers to reach Wuhan citizens'dining tables.

It was a working-class machine, a thousand-person hospital, built 24 hours a day, 10 days.

Nearly all the employees of 42 Changyuan sanitary material enterprises in Henan Province gave up their rest and rushed to work 24 hours a day. Workers were paid up to five times the maximum wage and administrators were paid three times as much. When they started, they lost money, but from entrepreneurs to production workers, they all rushed to Wuhan's aid.

A People's Liberation Army Transport Support Team, comprising 130 military trucks and more than 260 officers and soldiers, has appeared on the streets of Wuhan. Starting from the 2nd, they will dispatch transport forces to ensure the daily distribution of goods and materials to Wuhan residents according to the daily demand of local distribution centers.

Economic experts are also predicting how China's economy will develop. In the short term, they argue, the economic impact is inevitable.

Ba Shusong, chief economist at the Asian Financial Association, thinks that current trends predict that GDP could fall to less than 5% in the first quarter of 2020.

Huang Jianhui, head of research at Minsheng Bank, said GDP growth in the first quarter was 4.5% year on year in the optimistic scenario, 4.0% year on year in the benchmark scenario and 3.4% year on year in the pessimistic scenario.

Dacheng Fund chief economist Yao Yudong pointed out that the post-festival delay in the resumption of business and other factors to China's first-quarter economic operation brought greater pressure.

Li Xunlei, chief economist of Zhongtai Securities Co. , said the short-term impact of the new crown disease on China's economy should not be underestimated, and problems that would not otherwise be a problem might arise.

In the long run, the long-term pro-cyclical trend of the economy remains unchanged. It's a Seek truth from facts attitude.

Even the lawyers came forward to help. On February 7, after the application of Wuhan Central Hospital, the Wuhan Municipal Bureau of Social Welfare made the decision of Armed Social Workers Insurance (2020) No. 010001"decision to identify work-related injuries, " which identified the death of Li Wenliang as work-related injuries.

According to the calculation, Comrade Li Wenliang's compensation for work-related injury insurance is as follows: A one-time death grant of 785,020 yuan and a funeral grant of 36,834 yuan. The Wuhan Central Hospital had taken out and paid the industrial injury insurance for Li before his death in accordance with the law. The industrial injury insurance benefits were paid by the Industrial Injury Insurance Fund.

A lawyer wrote an article to send out a reminder, "Wuhan Municipal Bureau of Social Welfare, did you give Dr. Li Wenliang 62,160 yuan less? ". The lawyer's reason is that the Wuhan Municipal Bureau of People's social welfare used 39,251 yuan of the disposable income in 2018. The 2019 figure ($42,359) should be used.

From anti-epidemic actions to anti-epidemic Spirit

Every major event, there will always be a valuable spiritual wealth, such as, "98 anti-flood Spirit. ". This time there will be "2020 anti-epidemic Spirit. ".

On February 6, the provincial department of Human Resources and Social Security, the provincial health commission issued the "decision on giving Zhang Dingyu and Comrade Zhang Jixian Great Merit Award. ". This is the first time this year.

Zhang Dingyu is currently the director of Wuhan Infectious Disease Hospital in Wuhan. He faced the pneumonia epidemic, in the body with a serious disease (als) in the case of the front, lead the charge.

Zhang Jixian was the first to sound the alarm for epidemic prevention and control work.

There was also a doctor, very ordinary, but very great, dare to tell the truth, is the first outbreak of "whistle-blower. ". He's dead. The world mourns him. He is Dr Li Wenliang.

At 2:58 a.m. on February 7, a wechat message was sent from Wuhan's Central Hospital: Eye Doctor Li Wenliang, who had contracted pneumonia in the fight against COVID-19 infection, died after his condition deteriorated.

The Internet is a sad, Red Candle lit.

The official Sina Weibo Account of the World Health Organization (WHO) posted a message at 12:33 on February 7, paying tribute to the late Dr. Li Wenliang and expressing condolences to his family.

State Health Commission, Hubei Health Commission, Wuhan Municipal Government, Wuhan Health Commission issued a notice of mourning.

I think the Wuhan University should establish him as an "outstanding alumnus" and write "dare to speak out" into the spirit of the university.

News came at noon on the 7th: With the approval of the Central Committee, the State Supervision Commission decided to send an investigation team to Wuhan, Hubei Province, to conduct a comprehensive investigation into the problems related to Dr. Li Wenliang reported by the public.

Today, more than 80,000 military and medical personnel in and outside the province are fighting on the front line for the safety of the people of Wuhan. They're tired, misunderstood, even sacrificed. They are qualified "fighters" .

Some departments asked me, what do you have in mind?

I propose to call the southern mouth of ChinaTG. A "2020 Wuhan anti-epidemic theme park" . Li Wenliang is the first statue.

From dealing with public opinion to dealing with public opinion

The Central Government's Politburo Standing Committee of the Communist Party of China on the 3rd, in particular, stressed the need to do a good job in publicity, education and public opinion guidance, coordinating online and offline, domestic and international affairs, Major and minor issues, and building confidence, heartwarming the people and collecting people's hearts.

However, when it comes to a critical moment, every move, every word and every action of officials at all levels will cause fluctuations in public opinion. This "new type of pneumonia" is also a typical case.

The authorities asked me how to solve the current crisis of public opinion. My advice is to try to get out of the press conference, familiarize yourself with the content, and prepare only a few data cards. To attend a press conference in this way is a guide to the media, so that we can see the self-confidence and determination of officers at all levels. As a result, netizens appreciate the ease with which the mayor of Wenzhou and the vice mayor of Hangzhou handled the situation.

In the cadre ability promotion aspect, also must avoid "the ability vacancy" the question. On February 6th the Discipline Inspection Commission of Hubei Province and the Organization Department of the Provincial Party Committee issued a notice calling for a vigorous crackdown on formalism and bureaucracy in the prevention and control of the epidemic, to ensure that the Party Central Committee, the State Council, the Central Commission for Discipline Inspection and Provincial Party committees, provincial governments to implement the detailed deployment measures.

In fact, it is also necessary to improve the ability to deal with public opinion, to deal with the lack of public opinion, but also a kind of bureaucracy.

Therefore, I suggest that cadres at all levels be trained to deal with public opinion. When and what to say is important. Apologies are good medicine when there is a lack of work.

For example, in the current situation, provincial and municipal leaders should stand up and say: Wuhan "new type of pneumonia" to the people across the country, people around the world to apologize for the trouble. As early as 2007, the Shenzhen municipal government stipulated that anyone who made a mistake should apologize first.

From anti-epidemic to anti-epidemic economy

With the end of the Spring Festival holiday, the Lantern Festival after the resumption of economic activities in various places, it should be anti-epidemic and economic development. At the very least, fighting the epidemic should not be a reason to hold back the economy.

It's understandable that so many places are blocking the roads to prevent infection. However, blocking the normal economic circulation is also a very dangerous thing. Some media write articles called, pig farms, chicken farms have seen the bottom of the feed. This caused the Public Security Bureau to take notice and not allow the circuit to be broken.

After the road was cleared, the problem was alleviated. However, the chicken farm and sold out of the chicken, the boss had to bury alive every day. When one problem is solved, new problems arise.

Luckily, the Public Security Bureau stopped it in time. If because fight epidemic disease to affect economic activity artificially, that is tantamount to"add insult to injury".

On July 7, the joint prevention and Control Mechanism of the State Council held a press conference to introduce relevant fiscal and tax policies to support the prevention and control of COVID-19 pneumonia and ease the financing difficulties of small and micro enterprises.

This is particularly helpful for small and medium-sized enterprises, which mention in particular:

This affected by the larger epidemic, such as transportation, catering, accommodation, tourism, including express, civil aviation and other industries to value-added tax, corporate income tax and other tax concessions.

Full pre-tax deduction for corporate and individual donations.

The bank in the credit policy to be affected by the epidemic people to give a proper tilt. Such as flexible adjustment of housing mortgage, credit card personal loan repayment arrangements, insurance institutions to give priority to new patients with pneumonia out of insurance claims.

Increase credit loans and medium-and long-term loans, reduce the cost of comprehensive financing.

Enterprises temporarily affected by the epidemic are not blindly taking loans, cutting off loans and pressing loans.

All this is conducive to the resumption of business production, the people restore confidence.

From explaining remorse to deep reflection

At a Government of the People's Republic of China News Conference on the evening of January 26th, the governor said he felt sorry, guilty and remorse about the outbreak. Since then, several leaders have said the same thing.

It is not enough to grieve, to feel guilty, and to blame oneself for the current disaster. You need to think deep down.

The Politburo Standing Committee of the Communist Party of China meeting on Feb. 3 stressed that the outbreak is a major test of China's governance system and capacity, and we must sum up the experience and draw lessons. In view of the shortcomings and shortcomings exposed in the response to the epidemic, we should improve the national emergency management system and enhance the ability to deal with urgent and difficult tasks. Must carry on the thorough investigation and the rectification to the public health environment, makes up the Public Health Short Board.

From the government level, how to think deeply?

It is necessary to improve the ability of governments at all levels to respond to public health and safety, to have an epidemic notification system with the active participation of medical personnel, to trust the views of medical experts, and to have contingency plans, especially in terms of material reserves.

I suggest that, like frozen pork, masks, protective clothing, goggles and other materials, the implementation of an order-based procurement, within a specified period of time, production enterprises can provide the number of supplies. This is the "hidden for enterprise" . Government grants reserve costs.

At the level of cadres and management, medical experts must be attached to the leading bodies at all levels, for example, medical experts should be included among the vice-governors, vice-mayors and vice-county heads; the directors of the health committees at all levels should stop production and study for six months in the public health of Medical Universities; Let the personnel who know hygiene and health take care of hygiene and health. As Ren Zhengfei said, "let those who hear the sound of the cannon call out the fire! " "Let those who can hear the sound of the cannon direct the battle. ". In this way, we can rest assured. Otherwise, it will repeat the tragedy of the Health Commission Director "not knowing everything" .

At the level of the common people, we should make "wash hands frequently, wear masks, measure body temperature, and teach hygiene" become a virtue of the Chinese nation.

I live in north Fujian small town, for masks, childhood impression is, put on a mask, the face is not cold. 30 years ago, I had a baby, and gauze masks became bibs for eating. Now, hopefully, masks will become the norm. Japan next door is a nation that likes to wear masks.

Summary

In a few days, said Academician Zhong Nanshan, we will see an inflection point.

By February 6th, the first 14 days had passed. By the 20th, 14 days from now, things will be much better. Let us work together and look forward to it!

At the time of this writing, Wuhan had a sunny day after two days of cloudy and rainy weather. Is that a good sign?
